cs.AR, cs.ET, cs.DC, cs.NE, cs.SY

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.AR (Computational Biology and Bioinformatics) as it presents a novel architecture for biological sequence alignment. It may also belong to cs.ET (Emerging Technologies) as it introduces a new processing-in-memory architecture based on resistive content addressable memory. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it discusses the limitations of traditional von Neumann architectures and proposes a massively parallel non-von Neumann architecture. Finally, it could be classified under cs.SY (Systems and Control) as it presents an algorithm for associative processing on the BioSEAL architecture.
